   rdfs:comment """We included this axiom in accordance to the ChEBI-BFO alignment, findable here: https://ftp.ebi.ac.uk/pub/databases/chebi/archive/chebi_legacy/ontology/chebi-in-bfo.owl 

Source: https://ftp.ebi.ac.uk/pub/databases/chebi/archive/chebi_legacy/ontology/

Reference: Hastings J, De Matos P, Dekker A, Ennis M, Harsha B, Kale N, et al. The ChEBI reference database and ontology for biologically relevant chemistry: enhancements for 2013. Nucleic Acids Res. 2012 Nov 23;41(D1):D456–63."""@en
 ] .


###  http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/CHEBI_60027
<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/CHEBI_60027> owl:equivalentClass :ClimOO_0000246 ;
                                             rdfs:comment """ClimOO Ontology comment:
ChEBI covers several subclasses that may be relevant for inclusion, such as polyester or rubber polymer materials. We refer users to ChEBI for importing as needed."""@en .


###  http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/COB_0000035
<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/COB_0000035> rdfs:comment """ClimOO Ontology comment: 
Currently, we focus the following ClimOO classes on completely executed processes. Implementations can enhance the model to account for processes that might fail."""@en .


