###  https://www.w3id.org/climoo#ClimOO_0000073
:ClimOO_0000073 rdf:type owl:NamedIndividual ,
                         <https://www.w3id.org/sco#SCO_0000016> ;
                <http://purl.org/dc/terms/description> "This owl:NamedIndividual tracks the framework view proposed by Hartmann et al. (2019)."@en ;
                <http://purl.org/dc/terms/source> "Hartmann, N. B., Hüffer, T., Thompson, R. C., Hassellöv, M., Verschoor, A., Daugaard, A. E., Rist, S., Karlsson, T., Brennholt, N., Cole, M., Herrling, M. P., Hess, M. C., Ivleva, N. P., Lusher, A. L., & Wagner, M. (2019). Are We Speaking the Same Language? Recommendations for a Definition and Categorization Framework for Plastic Debris. Environmental Science & Technology, 53(3), 1039–1047. https://doi.org/10.1021/acs.est.8b05297" ;
                rdfs:comment """See the following standards concerning microplastic classification. They recommend using the same size range as Hartmann et al. (2019) of 1 and 1000 µm in its largest dimension.
ISO/TR 21960:2020Plastics — Environmental aspects — State of knowledge and methodologies https://www.iso.org/standard/72300.html
ISO 4484-1:2023Textiles and textile products — Microplastics from textile sources Part 1: Determination of material loss from fabrics during washing https://www.iso.org/standard/82238.html"""@en ;
                rdfs:label "Hartmann et al. perspective on microplastics"@en .

